<br><br>There’s less than 1% of people who have met ‘The One', who never experienced a breakup but lived happily ever after. Even that 1% will end that relationship at some point when they pass away.
<br>And, for the majority of us who don’t strike gold the first time around, we’re going to have to deal with breakups and the trials and tribulations of romance. We’ll probably find ourselves in a toxic relationship for too long. We’ll probably get cheated on at least once. We’ll probably have our hearts smashed into a million pieces when we discover that someone ‘No longer loves us anymore.’ These are the REALITIES of the human condition.
<br>But, finding love is about understanding that you need to end your current relationship to find out what the real one. All breakups suck in the beginning until you grow and move on. That's time to find yourself. Once you find yourself, the heart will be ready for love again. How you move forward from there is up to you.

